Egypt Stocks: EFG-Hermes, Orascom Construction, Orascom Telecom

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-09-20T13:14:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/egypt-stocks-efg-hermes-orascom-construction-orascom-telecom.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
gained 1.2 percent to 4,463.74, the highest level in almost a
week, at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY) gained 2.5 percent to
16.51 Egyptian pounds, the highest level since Sept. 12. The
biggest publicly traded Arab investment bank said it will
distribute one free share for every four held to shareholders as
of Oct. 2.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   advanced 1
percent to 234.2 pounds, the highest close in a week. A joint
venture between BESIX Group, a unit of Egypt’s biggest builder,
and Al-Muhaidib Contracting Co. won a 380 million-euro ($519
million) contract to design and construct King Abdullah Sports
City near Jeddah.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)   climbed 5.2 percent
to 3.62 pounds, the highest level since Aug. 4. North Africa’s
biggest mobile-network operator was rated new “overweight” at
 Barclays Capital , which said the company’s Algerian unit may be
undervalued. The price estimate for the company’s London-listed
global depository receipts was set at $4.4. They advanced 3.3
percent to $3 at 2:06 p.m. in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
